          <p class="supertitle">Full Time / Culver City, CA</p>
  <h1>Senior Flex Developer at Riot Games</h1>

  <div class="columns generic ">
    <div class="column main">
      <p>As one of the most popular PC games today, League of Legends is reshaping PC gaming and core gamers perception of virtual goods. Riot Games (named a Top 30 developer by Game Developer Magazine), the publisher and developer of League of Legends, is experiencing a period of rapid growth, doubling the size of the company in the past year. With over 4 MM players in their debut title across the US and Europe, and numerous awards (including IGN.com’s Readers' Choice for Best Multiplayer Game for League of Legends), Riot Games has also pioneered an innovative live development model and is looking to expand its production capabilities.</p>

<p>Currently, we have a great opportunity for a Senior Flex Developer in our Los Angeles, CA office. If you want to work in a fun, fast-paced and creatively challenging environment, this is the place for you. The ideal candidate will be able to manage their time effectively while they design and implement exciting and intuitive interface elements.</p>

<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>

<p>•Help design and implement intuitive and exciting User Interfaces</p>

<p>•Write, test and debug User Interface code for our products</p>

<p>•Rapidly prototype and iterate User Interface element and flows</p>

<p>•Liaise with designers, producers, and artists to implement new UI features</p>

<p>•Write clear, clean, readable, portable, reliable, and manageable code</p>

<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>

<p>•Proven experience architecting and developing rich client applications</p>

<p>•Excellent knowledge of UI architectural patterns</p>

<p>•Significant experience writing automated unit and functional tests</p>

<p>•High degree of proficiency writing rich client code with Java, Flex 3, and/or Air 1.5</p>

<p>•Experience mentoring junior developers</p>

<p>•Experience with end user usability paradigms for web and desktop applications</p>

<p>•Creativity and the ability to design and implement intuitive interfaces</p>

<p>•Positive, self starting, team-oriented attitude</p>

<p>•Must be legally authorized or able to obtain legal authorization to work in the US</p>

<p><strong>Desired:</strong></p>

<p>•Experience in an Agile development team</p>

<p>•Has a demonstrated interest or experience in the game industry</p>

<p>•User Experience design experience for games or other media</p>

<p>•Proficiency with Actionscript 3 and Flash 9/10</p>

<p>•Experience with server-side Java development, including use of Spring Framework, Hibernate, Oracle Coherence</p>

<p>•Experience with Adobe LCDS</p>

<p>•Development experience with front-end web development technologies including:
 JavaScript
 XHTML
 CSS</p>

<p>•Familiarity with Scaleform GFX</p>

<p>If you are an experienced UI developer who wants the opportunity to with a creative and talented team and have a positive, &ldquo;can do" attitude, we want to hear from you!</p>

<p>Riot games is paying salaries that are competitive with the enterprise software industry.</p>

<p>NO RECRUITERS. NO PHONE CALLS. WE DO NOT ACCEPT WALK-INS OR PHONE CALLS TO OUR OFFICE, FAILURE TO FOLLOW THIS DIRECTIVE WILL RESULT IN IMMEDIATE DISQUALIFICATION FROM ANY POSITION AT RIOT GAMES.</p>
</div><!-- /.column.main -->

